result.name: OMA

reviews.text: Nice bar, lots of people but not too crowded. While the music at the night I went is not my type. And the people are not too wild. Just gentle waving, dancing.

Go to this club if you want to have all your belongings stolen. Me and my friends got all our phones and wallets stolen in front of the OMA, just in front of the security guy who didn't do anything. Even the managers of the club didn't help us or tried to call the police and left us on our own. Maybe all corrupted and work all together.
After talking to people in Hong Kong, it seems like this is not an isolated case at OMA. It happened to many people and every time OMA is not doing anything.

4 Stars because the music is great for those that listen to deep house, tech house, progressive house. The venue is small but it’s not too packed. No 5 stars because Drinks are pricey, and because the staff is not very friendly. Not busy until 1:30/2:00am. Free entry before 00:00.
SO F’KIN’ BAD. Saturday night charge 100HKD, expensive drinks, music solely for ppl who want to space out mindlessly, smokers inside letting it all fume out. Ugh.
Cosy and fun, great music and vibe.
